&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;facebook_like_button&#34; style=&#34;float: left; vertical-align: top; margin-left: 10px; max-width: 255px&#34;&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I had a user ask to pay his Sensr.net bill in &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Main_Page&#34; title=&#34;Bitcoin Wiki&#34;&gt;Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;. We use Stripe to process payments and t&lt;a href=&#34;https://stripe.com/bitcoin&#34; title=&#34;Stripe and Bitcoin&#34;&gt;hey don&amp;#8217;t yet support Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;.  However a friend recommended Coinbase, so I set up a merchant page there where you can &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.coinbase.com/sensr&#34; title=&#34;Sensr.net Bitcoin Page&#34;&gt;pay Sensr.net in Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;#8217;re interested in paying your Sensr.net bill using Bitcoin, just let us know.  If you already have a Sensr.net account, just pay us in Bitcoin and we&amp;#8217;ll add the credit to your account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions on this, just drop us an email to billing at Sensr.net.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

